			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Army of the Dead</span>
<br />

<br />
As discussed in many threads across this board, i have a suggestion for the REP to bring to the dev.
<br />

<br />
As per already stated, here are the facts i've been able to gather so far
<br />
(please if i got some of this wrong post i'll ammend this thread)
<br />

<br />
-----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
AoD require WTD 3
<br />
AoD timer is link to WTD timer preventing from using both
<br />
AoD DPS of 1 body compare to WTD DPS of 1 body is lower
<br />
AoD 1 Duration is lower then WTD 3 
<br />
AoD needs 1 body for each raised body (meaning 5 body for 5 pet)
<br />
AoD pets do not cast spells
<br />

<br />
-----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
To try and make this a constructive document to help the REP, here are some Idea on how to fix this AA, "i" think could be inplimented.
<br />

<br />
-----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">OPTION 1</span> - Upgrade to WTD  - up to 5 body needed</span>
<br />
Cost Per Rank: 3/3/3/3 
<br />
Number of Rank: 4
<br />
Scale rank from 67 to 70 (one per lvl)
<br />

<br />
Each Rank gives ability to raise 1 more body in same time.
<br />
AoD require 1 body per pet up to 5 pets;
<br />
AoD duration remain 90 sec;
<br />
AoD DPS/HP for 1 pet is the same as per WTD pet;
<br />
AoD pets can cast spells;
<br />
AoD is on same timer as WTD;
<br />
AoD pets looks like its raised target.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Short description:</span> Same as WTD but ya get more pet if there is more bodies around. Making WTD useless. This would generate somewhat lots of DPS, so i supposed there is room to adjust the DPS and HP of each Pets in relation with WTD so that 1 AoD and 1 WTD are equal.
<br />

<br />
-----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">OPTION 2</span> - Upgrade to WTD - 1 body needed</span>
<br />
Cost Per Rank: 3/3/3/3
<br />
Number of Rank: 4
<br />
Scale rank from 67 to 70 (one per lvl)
<br />

<br />
Each Rank gives ability to raise 1 more body in same time.
<br />
AoD require only 1 body to raise up to 5 pets;
<br />
AoD duration remain 90 sec;
<br />
AoD DPS/HP for 1 pet is the same as per WTD pet;
<br />
AoD pets can cast spells;
<br />
AoD is on a same timer as WTD;
<br />
AoD pets looks like shadows.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Short description:</span> This would be more like a take the essence from a dead body to generate the pets idea. This would generate somewhat lots of DPS, so i supposed there is room to adjust the DPS and HP of each Pets in relation with WTD so that 1 AoD and 1 WTD are equal.
<br />

<br />
-----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">OPTION 3</span> - AoD (Shadow) - up to 5 body needed</span>
<br />
Cost Per Rank: 3/3/3/3/3
<br />
Number of Rank: 5
<br />
Scale rank from 66 to 70 (one per lvl)
<br />

<br />
Each Rank gives ability to raise 1 shadow.
<br />
AoD require 1 body per pet up to 5 pets;
<br />
AoD duration would be 30/45/60/75/90 sec;
<br />
AoD DPS/HP for 1 pet would be different then WTD pet (suggesting lower);
<br />
AoD pets can cast spells;
<br />
AoD is on a different timer then WTD;
<br />
AoD pets looks like small shadows.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Short description:</span> This would create a more balance AA while retaining the WTD ability. Would be lots easier to code from their end im' sure and well sound more realistic.
<br />

<br />
-----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">OPTION 4</span> - AoD (Shadow) - 1 body needed</span>
<br />
Cost Per Rank: 3/3/3/3/3
<br />
Number of Rank: 5
<br />
Scale rank from 66 to 70 (one per lvl)
<br />

<br />
Each Rank gives ability to raise 1 shadow.
<br />
AoD require only 1 body to raise up to 5 pets;
<br />
AoD duration would be 30/45/60/75/90 sec;
<br />
AoD DPS/HP for 1 pet would be different then WTD pet (suggesting lower);
<br />
AoD pets can cast spells;
<br />
AoD is on a different timer then WTD;
<br />
AoD pets looks like small shadows.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Short description:</span> This would create a more balance AA while retaining the WTD ability. Would be lots easier to code from their end im' sure and well sound more realistic.
<br />

<br />
-----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
My choise is on <span style="font-weight: bold">option 1</span>.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: darkred">Virun Waulfebane</span></span>
